edu.wpi.cs.jburge.SEURAT.editors
Class SelectCandidatePatterns

java.lang.Object
  edu.wpi.cs.jburge.SEURAT.editors.SelectCandidatePatterns

public class SelectCandidatePatterns
extends java.lang.Object

This class presents the user the GUI to select patterns given a list of available pattern problem categories.
There are two locations where we need this: when we're doing candidate pattern selection in rationale explorer and selecting sub-patterns of some pattern in pattern library.
As such, there are two constructors for this class. I have a "setupForm" function to set up the basic GUI, and then do the actions, depending on the input of available patterns seperately in the constructor.
